This paper proposes novel attention operators for graph representation learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on improving the efficiency and performance of graph attention operators, which are commonly used in computer vision, natural language processing, and network embedding learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
